fields.headline: Dutch tests could set up battle of Britain
fields.bodyText: Leeds and Rangers, the only remaining British sides in this season's Uefa Cup, will face each other at the quarter-final stage if they can overcome Dutch opponents in February's fourth round, after yesterday's draw in Nyon. David O'Leary's side will face the Dutch champions PSV Eindhoven. Rangers, with their new manager Alex McLeish at the helm, will play Feyenoord, both ties' first legs taking place in the Netherlands. Both clubs dropped down from the Champions League. Leeds and Rangers met in the European Cup in 1992; Rangers won both legs 2-1. McLeish is set to become the first manager in Scot land to take charge of two different teams in the same European competition in the same season. Fourth round : Milan v Roda JC; Lille v Borussia Dortmund; Valencia v Servette; PSV Eindhoven v Leeds; Lyon v Slovan Liberec; Hapoel Tel-Aviv v Parma; Internazionale v AEK Athens; Rangers v Feyenoord Ties to be played on February 21 and 28. Quarter-finals : Hapoel Tel-Aviv/Parma v Milan/Roda; Internazionale/AEK Athens v Valencia/Servette; PSV Eindhoven/Leeds v Rangers/Feyenoord; Lyon/Slovan Liberec v Lille/Borussia Dortmund Ties to be played on March 14 and 21.
